<recipe>
<title>
Cranberry Yogurt Muffins
</title>
<details>

</details>
<ingredients>
1 cup whole wheat flour
1/2 cup all-purpose flour
1 teaspoon baking soda
3/4 teaspoon baking powder
1/4 teaspoon salt
1 large egg
1/3 cup granulated sugar
1/3 cup vegetable oil
1/3 cup milk low-fat ok
1 cup fat-free vanilla Greek yogurt
1 lemon zested
3/4 cup dried cranberries roughly chopped
2 tablespoons chopped pecans optional
2 tablespoons raw sugar optional
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Preheat oven to 375 F. Grease or line a 12-cup muffin tin. Set aside.
In a medium bowl, whisk together flours, baking soda, baking powder, and salt. Set aside.
In a large bowl, beat together egg and sugar.
Stir in oil, milk, yogurt, and lemon zest.
Add flour mixture, and stir until just combined.
Fold in cranberries.
Scoop batter into muffin cups.
Top with chopped pecans and raw sugar, if using.
Bake for 18-25 minutes, or until lightly browned and top springs back when lightly pushed.
</instructions>
</recipe>
